Description.Text: This is a pleasant hotel, typical of the majority in Bayswater. 09/07RP

The hotel is situated in Bayswater, close to Paddington Station and just five minutes from Queensway and Lancaster Gate underground stations, which give easy access to the Westend. Hyde Park is also just five minutes walk away.

The rooms are small on average, both the bedrooms and bathrooms are in fair condition, decorated mainly in pinks they are pleasantly cosy. It should be noted that the hotel has a constant renovation policy so the quality of the rooms is always kept to a very high standard.
The building is made up of several Victorian townhouses with an attractive white facade.
The restaurant is simply decorated in pale pinks with modern furniture and adjoins the unusual bar decorated in a stylish pale green. They serve good quality Malaysian food.
The lobby has been recently renovated and is light, airy, and welcoming, decorated in peach, gold and cream with pale wood panelling and unusual modern chandeliers.
